
This is an attempt to port recent glibc-2.3.x for kfreebsd.
It is based on previous work for glibc 2.3.0.

As glibc source is used a post-2.3.6 snapshot, available from
ftp://sources.redhat.com/pub/glibc/snapshots/glibc-2.3-20051212.tar.bz2

The main part are new arch specific files, 
linked into glibc-2.3.x tree as follows:

sysdeps/kfreebsd
	-> $SRC/sysdeps/unix/bsd/bsd4.4/kfreebsd

linuxthreads/kfreebsd
	-> $SRC/linuxthreads/sysdeps/unix/bsd/bsd4.4/kfreebsd

Remaining part are miscellaneous kfreebsd changes and hacks,
stored in dir patches. 




			glibc-2.3 			glibc-2.3-head
===============================================================================
glibc base		2.3.0				2.3.6
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
gcc			3.3.x				4.0.x
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
kernel headers		kfreebsd5-headers		kfreebsd-kernel-headers
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
sysdeps			external in glibc-kbsd		integrated into glibc
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
thread local storage	no				yes
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
arch i386		yes				yes
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
arch amd64		no				yes
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
arch alpha		???				???
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Status of 2.3.6:
================

i386	- looks fine, uploaded in unreleased

amd64	- able to build, not tested

alpha	- not even tried to build

